======================================================================
PALEY P_7: DETAILED DUALITY ANALYSIS
======================================================================
  Anti-automorphism: x ↦ 3x mod 7
  φ(v_0,...,v_m) = (3*v_m, ..., 3*v_0) mod 7

  Testing φ: A_m → A_{p-1-m} bijection:

  P_7 Ω/7 = [1, 3, 6, 9, 9, 6, 3]
  Reversed = [3, 6, 9, 9, 6, 3, 1]
  Ω_0/7 = 1, Ω_6/7 = 3  — NOT equal
  Ω_1/7 = 3, Ω_5/7 = 6  — NOT equal
  The palindrome claim was WRONG for P_7!

  P_5 Ω/5 = [1, 2, 2, 2, 1]
  This IS palindromic: Ω_0=Ω_4, Ω_1=Ω_3

  Checking sub-palindromes:
    [3,6,9,9,6,3] palindromic? True
    The TAIL Ω_1..Ω_6 = [3,6,9,9,6,3] IS palindromic!
    Only Ω_0 breaks the palindrome.

  P_5: Ω_1..Ω_3 = [10, 10, 10], palindromic? True
  P_7: Ω_1..Ω_5 = [21, 42, 63, 63, 42], palindromic? False

